item.description:
I kinda hate the default Alt+Tab switcher in Pantheon, so I use Rofi to fix that. This is how to use rofi as Alt+Tab switcher. Make sure you have rofi version 1.6.1 installed for this to work propperly.
Create a new scriptfile called alttab.sh with this content:
#!/usr/bin/env bash xdotool mousemove 960 540 &amp;&amp; rofi -no-config -theme alttab -kb-cancel &#34;Alt+Escape,Escape&#34; -kb-accept-entry &#39;!Alt-Tab,!Alt+Down,!Alt+ISO_Left_Tab,!Alt+Up,Return,!Alt+Alt_L&#39; -kb-row-down &#39;Alt-Tab,Alt+Down,Down,ISO_Left_Tab&#39; -kb-row-up &#39;Alt+ISO_Left_Tab,Alt+Up,Up&#39; -show window -selected-row 1 exit Now make it executable:
